After watching the latest Barbie movie I’m reminded about the importance of representation. While it’s a good somewhat nostalgic movie; it left me wanting for more. 

More representation of us; people that look like you and I; there where 2 plus size Barbie’s that had speaking roles in the movie, Nicola Coughlan and Sharon Rooney; don’t get me wrong they killed their roles but I still felt like i wanted to see someone that looked like me in the movie; I know some people may say be happy they included us Atall; and we’ve come along way to even be included but my thought process is have we? 

I stumbled on a Reddit discussion board talking about the plus size representation in the movie and how excited they were to see someone that looks like them and has their job title etc and first thought that came to mind was I ddnt. And that’s sad to think. Let’s not even get into the fact that the plus size Barbie’s that do exist have the smallest arms like the rest of us that don’t have small arms don’t “fit”. It’s 2023. To keep this caption from being even longer I will just say WE NEED MORE REPRESENTATION. #barbie #barbiemovie #barbie2023

If you’re looking for a new hobbie; then I highly recommend Golf. It’s fun, and a good workout especially if you don’t like to workout. I sleep like a baby after a golf game 

Here are 10 benefits of playing Golf: 

-Good for your heart
Studies have shown that walking an average of 2.5 hours per day can help reduce the risk of heart attacks by 30-40 percent. In an average round of 18-hole golf, players walk a total of over 10000 steps, which equates to roughly 8km and about 2 hours of walking depending on your stride and speed. All the more reasons to quit that gym membership and play golf every day. 

-Exercise
Walk a full-length 18 holes of golf can help you burn 1,200 calories, which allows you to stay fit and healthy. A golf swing is a full-body workout. Major muscle groups like your arms, legs, back, abdomen, chest, and shoulders are all engaged during a golf swing.
An average golf hole is around 300 to 400 meters. The incline and declining slope terrain of all golf courses will definitely burn that high calories cereal you had this morning after your first hole. 

-Low Risk Sport
Golf is widely recognized as a low-risk sport compared to many other sports. There’s less stress on the joints as the swings can be adjusted accordingly to each player.
The games can be played at your own pace and for longer periods of time, which is a unique characteristic of golf. The chances of a sports injury are definitely lower in comparisons to other sports like Basketball or Badminton. 

-Reduces Stress and Anxiety
Golf is an open-air sport that is surrounded by nature. With plenty of access to fresh air and Vitamin D, endorphin and serotonin levels are improved significantly, which helps with reducing stress and anxiety while also improving mood.
The pleasing greenery and fresh air also calm the mind which helps with focus and mental relaxation. As golf is a game where you are usually battling against yourself, it can be therapeutic to train your mind to relax and not to worry about work, only your golf game matters right now.

My Amazon list is in my story. I wrote this on the 29th of SEPT (12:36am) Transparent post. I’ve been MIA for 2 months (it’s actually a month. Lol felt like 2) and the world ddnt end. cause like I say to my friends and family. LA has been LA’ing. And if I’m being honest I just ddnt feel like posting content pretending like everything was rosy when it wasn’t. I had to move out. And finding a new apartment was proving difficult; To say the least. I was applying and getting denied, not because my credit is bad. Far from it. But because i don’t have a long enough credit history, so God kept REDIRECTING me. And I was fighting my hardest not to get frustrated. On the 29th at 12:39am in the morning almost 1am. I sat on my bed and wrote this testimony. Yes a testimony before it happened. Because the song firm foundation by maverick city and chandler more. The song in this video was ringing in my head and stayed on repeat. And I had peace that made no sense. I was telling my friend @whoistonye I can’t explain it. I have peace in this matter. It doesn’t even make sense. Anybody else in this situation would have broken down. But I JUST KNEW. THAT MY LIFE IS BUILT ON JESUS. AND HE’S NEVER LET ME DOWN!!!! At some point I texted friends like should I just come to Houston and stay with family while i look for a job since strike you know. It was a thought process that rained true for all of 30mins. And the peace came back. So at this hour. Now 12:44 I made a promise to God. I said LORD WHEN YOU DO THIS FOR ME YOUR DAUGHTER. WHEN YOU GIVE ME THE PLACE THAT IS FOR ME. I WILL TESTIFY ON SOCIAL MEDIA SEEING AS THATS WHERE I MAKE THE MOST NOISE. AND ILL LET EVERYONE KNOW HOW SWEET IT IS TO SERVE YOU!!! So I’m here testifying I’m currently in my new place. So prepare to be sick of me!!! All the home upgrades, decor posts are coming. But first. I’ll share this is take down of my rental friendly upgrades or if you’re staying with family and need extra space. GOD IS AMAZING. BELIEVE IT!!

I failed at reelsmas this year. Because birthday celebrations and working had me beat. But I’m determined to finish strong. So here’s a lil it’s bit from the decorations I did this year in our home.
